Figure out average sentence/paragraph/email size and mimic it.
Format the generated text to look like an email
Pull in other data sources:
  - facebook
  - twitter
  - google groups
  - slack
Pick a "topic word", and expand sentences in either direction from there, occaisionally coming back to the
topic word.
Use TFIDF to match up emails about specific topics, and use those as a more targetted corpus

Basic process
- user gives url to mailman archives
- download and cache mailman archives.  Don't redownload
- Choose which email address from a list - sort by frequency
- Generate a sample email, with a refresh button
